Title: Object: Portraits of Five Noble Admirals
Description: Five portraits, of Admirals Howe, St Vincent, Nelson, Duncan and Mitchell, all in uniform, almost half-length in ovals, Nelson in the centre with a crown above his oval and an anchor below it, three-quarter to left, the other four in the corners, directed three-quarter inwards. 1799 Mezzotint
Bibliographic references: Chaloner Smith 1883 / British Mezzotinto portraits from the introduction of the art to the early part of the present century (undescribed)
Russell 1926 / English Mezzotint Portraits and their states: Catalogue of Corrections of and Additions to Chaloner Smith's "British Mezzotinto Portraits" (1a) (Engraver not ascertained: Class III)
Associated names: Portrait of: Adm Richard Howe, Earl Howe
Portrait of: John Jervis, Earl of St Vincent
Portrait of: Horatio Nelson, 1st Baron and Viscount Nelson
Portrait of: Adam Duncan, 1st Viscount Duncan
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: William Meriton Eaton, 2nd Baron Cheylesmore
